cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DS

This paper discusses a privacy-preserving blockchain system and proposes a differential privacy framework for ring signature schemes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves optimization problems and algorithms, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions the concept of differential privacy, which could relate to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
